cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with image caption generation using neural networks, which is a problem in computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses training the model using backpropagation and variational lower bound, which are techniques used in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper evaluates its model on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR a possible sub-category.
